The fungal mage is a monster found in the Polypore Dungeon. If players come within one square away from it, it will infect them, dealing fast hits of 15-17 life points. However, this can be prevented by using neem oil on it. The fungal magi has a large damage reduction against ranged and melee attacks, causing these attacks to do a maximum of 50 life points.

Fungal mages have the highest drop rate for fungal flakes, and are known for dropping large amounts of potato cacti quite frequently.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 22 November 2012 (Update):
    • Fungal Mage now work correctly as Slayer Creatures, including giving the buffs from the Slayer Helm when on task.
  • update 28 November 2011 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • When the fungal mage is assigned as a Slayer task, when you block it you can also choose the option to block all monsters in the Polypore dungeon.
  • As of 1 February 2018, the highest kill count for these monsters was 259,437 kills, shared with all polypore creatures.[1]
    • This had increased to 351,360 by 6 May 2018.[2]
  • Before Solak's model was developed, a fungal mage was used as a placeholder model for testing Solak's mechanics.
  • Fungal magi are the only Polypore creature that drops ashes as remains - all other creatures, barring the infested axe, drop bones as remains.
